   Stunning new 12" by Amorphous Androgynous AKA The Future Sound of
   London, on psychedlic remix duty for none other than Manchesters
   favourite indie rockers, Oasis. This is actually a 5 track release, but
   in typical FSOL style, all tracks are mixed together so i've just
   compiled it all as a single MP3 so you can enjoy the 22 minute epic in
   all it's glory.

   To these ears, it seems like the first section is the actual remix and
   the rest is Brian and Garry experimenting with their own sound.

   Part 3 (aka the piano and cello section) is my particular favourite and
   reminds me a bit of "All is Harvest" from AA's "Alice in Ultraland"
   album in 2005.


   01          Falling Down                                         22:26 min
               (A Monstrous Psychedelic Bubble Exploding in Your Mind)
